ni-Sirieix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrea_Spendolini-Sirieix\"}, {\"begin\": 314, \"end\": 321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8681538757061044, \"rank\": 0.14736480606730648, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sport|Olympics\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 243}, {\"ngram\": \"the youngest member\", \"from\": 286, \"to\": 305}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 336, \"to\": 351}, {\"ngram\": \"so little joy\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 400}, {\"ngram\": \"her first Olympic experience\", \"from\": 404, \"to\": 432}, {\"ngram\": \"another\", \"from\": 466, \"to\": 473}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How glad the young Londonder must be this morning that she got back on the board.\", \"from\": 477, \"to\": 558, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the young Londonder\", \"from\": 486, \"to\": 505}, {\"ngram\": \"the board\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 557}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paired with Lois Toulson, and with TV-famous father Fred Sirieix watching on at the side of the pool, the 19-year-old dove to women's 10-metre synchro bronze, Britain's first ever Olympic medal in the event.\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 767, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 572, \"end\": 584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lois_Toulson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lois Toulson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lois_Toulson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lois_Toulson\"}, {\"begin\": 612, \"end\": 624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Sirieix\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fred Sirieix\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Sirieix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Sirieix\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the side\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 648}, {\"ngram\": \"the pool\", \"from\": 652, \"to\": 660}, {\"ngram\": \"the 19-year-old dove\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 682}, {\"ngram\": \"women's 10-metre synchro bronze\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 717}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 757, \"to\": 766}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am so happy I did not give up,\\\" she said, before heaping praise on her partner, for whom this was a first Olympic medal at her third Games.\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 911, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"praise\", \"from\": 829, \"to\": 835}, {\"ngram\": \"her partner\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 850}, {\"ngram\": \"a first Olympic medal\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 891}, {\"ngram\": \"her third Games\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 910}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I feel like I have grown as a person, not just an athlete, alongside Lois and she's taught me a lot.\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 1013, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 982, \"end\": 986, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lois_Griffin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.552434127517077e-13, \"text\": \"Lois\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lois_Griffin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lois_Griffin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a person\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 949}, {\"ngram\": \"not just an athlete\", \"from\": 951, \"to\": 970}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The medal can not describe how much I love Lois and love diving alongside her.\\\"\", \"from\": 1015, \"to\": 1095, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1059, \"end\": 1063, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lois_Griffin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.552434127517077e-13, \"text\": \"Lois\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lois_Griffin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lois_Griffin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The medal\", \"from\": 1016, \"to\": 1025}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Going into the final round, they had been fourth, but delivered their best dive of the day when it mattered most to climb a place, before a nervy wait for Canada's riposte ended with the Brits still ahead.\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1302, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1252, \"end\": 1258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9990412646149786, \"rank\": 0.0009233204756757623, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the final round\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1123}, {\"ngram\": \"their best dive\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1176}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1187}, {\"ngram\": \"a place\", \"from\": 1219, \"to\": 1226}, {\"ngram\": \"a nervy wait\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1247}, {\"ngram\": \"the Brits\", \"from\": 1280, \"to\": 1289}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At times in the past, Spendolini-Sirieix has been irritated at being spoken of constantly in relation to her father, but says she is at ease with it now.\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1457, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"times\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1312}, {\"ngram\": \"the past\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1324}, {\"ngram\": \"Spendolini-Sirieix\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1344}, {\"ngram\": \"relation\", \"from\": 1397, \"to\": 1405}, {\"ngram\": \"her father\", \"from\": 1409, \"to\": 1419}, {\"ngram\": \"ease\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1444}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As well as battling a bout of the 'twisties' in Tokyo - the same terrifying, mid-air mental block that hindered Simone Biles at the same Games - Spendolini-Sirieix struggled with loneliness as the pandemic kept her family away.\", \"from\": 1459, \"to\": 1686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1507, \"end\": 1512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999591460483247, \"rank\": 4.085548415182124e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"typ